# QA Review Expectations

Use this rule when performing a QA-style review of a PR.

## Core Rule

QA review must validate intended behavior, not just code style.

## QA Review Should Check

- issue alignment
- acceptance criteria coverage
- failure path handling (voice unrecognized, incomplete set, conflict, auth/session errors)
- regression risk (parsing, grouping, persistence, session lifecycle)
- lifecycle/state integrity (session, set, set group)
- persistence or data-integrity effects where relevant
- test adequacy (unit for parsing/grouping, integration for session/set, UI for key screens where applicable)
- documentation impact if behavior changed materially

## Structure Feedback As

- verdict
- scope check
- acceptance criteria check
- blocking findings
- non-blocking improvements
- missing validation or documentation

## Final Rule

A QA review that ignores behavior and focuses only on style is not doing the job this repository needs.
